{"questionId":"17433","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows part of the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2{x^2} = {\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^3}\\,y\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>si</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>n</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0 \\leqslant y \\leqslant \\pi \">\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c229d220b6ff75694fbace72de213427a66a989d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The shaded region <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"R\">\n  <mi>R</mi>\n</math></span> is the area bounded by the curve, the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>-axis and the lines <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 0\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = \\pi \">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the area of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"R\"> <mi>R</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = \\sqrt {\\frac{1}{2}{\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^3}\\,y} \"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <msqrt> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac>